To secure an AWS VPC using IAM policies, you can use the `ec2:Vpc` condition key to specify the full ARN of the VPC. For example, to allow a specific instance to view resources in other AWS services within a specific VPC, you can attach a policy with the following statement:

```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "*",
      "Resource": "*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringLike": {
          "ec2:Vpc": "arn:aws:ec2:*:*:vpc/vpc-ec43eb89"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

